1.	Why labels + for/id beat placeholders for accessibility and error prevention,

    It helps with screen readers and helps when the labels dont disappear when typing.

2.	What aria-describedby adds to helper text,

    It allows screen readers and such to read them to give extra guidance.

3.	One place where native validation improved UX (and one limitation).

    Nativ validation helps regulate the inputs such as email but I beleive it isn't fully customizable.